<controlled negatives>

SET UP:
-same set up as the cable bicep curl

TIPS:

⭕️lympia ‘22 was one for the books ❤️

From an outsiders perspective not being a competitor in the Olympia, I give each competitor so much credit. To even be able to qualify for the Olympia is such a huge accomplishment. There’s so much pressure, time, energy, commitment, and pushing past all mental and physical barriers to present the package that has been worked on and polished all year, and years prior leading up this moment. To be able to compete with the best in the world… is truly something special. Congratulations to all of the competitors this weekend. They set the standard and they are truly all superstars⭐️

It was really cool to see all of the hard work that was put into each booth. I remember being at a booth at the Arnold back in 2019 and seeing everyone participating to help put the booth together, because every detail mattered in order for the booth to look attractive for people to stop by. There is so much planning and work that goes into an expo and it does not go unnoticed. 

I am feeling very grateful for this weekend; being able to spend time with my friends and laughing so hard that nothing else mattered in that moment. The people make the party. Social media is a different world these days and it’s up to us to stay true to ourselves. We often search for validation, or bend ourselves to fit what we see others doing and I can promise you, changing yourself, or who you are deep down is not worth a social media following, likes, or views. Be yourself because no one can be you. 

Idek if this caption makes sense, I just feel very sentimental these days (well always) and wanted to share my thoughts. Happy Monday let’s have a great week ❤️

Sometimes I really don’t know how I got here.

I’m referring to who I’ve grown into as a person. 

I remember being this little girl with big hopes and dreams and had no idea how I was going to do anything. I think the biggest lesson I would give to anyone wanting to follow their dreams would be just do it. I honestly still to this day don’t really know what I’m doing haha, but I know I try and give my all for the day and that’s all you can really do.

School doesn’t really prepare you for life after it’s all said and done and I found myself getting smacked in the face with bills, problems, heart break, insecurities, and responsibilities I didn’t really know how to handle. There isn’t a written handbook on how to specifically live our life and that’s why it’s important we write our own story. We aren’t in control of everything, but we are in control of our behavior, our actions, our discipline, and our ability to learn after a failed attempt. 

I’m not perfect. I have flaws. We all do. I am just a human trying to inspire and learn as I go. I love having you here because it makes me feel less alone.

What you’ll need:
-Oats

How to make: 
-Cook your oats with your fruit, or toppings of choice. I prefer my oatmeal to be more on the liquid-ey side so I make sure the oats aren’t dry/thick after they are heated. 
-Cook in microwave for 2 minutes.
-Add your protein flavor of choice and mix! It is important that you do not cook the protein powder, only mix in after the oats are cooked! 

Vegan protein is also great for people that are lactose intolerant, or struggle with digesting animal sources of protein.

Normally, I try and make your birthday posts about how much I appreciate you being my M❤️M, but this year, I want to express how proud I am of you for your own mental and emotional growth. This past time while you stayed with me as I recovered from my surgery, we had lots of talks about boundaries, what respect means to us, and how to mutually agree to disagree; while having sincere empathy for what we may not comprehend in that moment. For those that don’t know, I’ve been in therapy about 13 years now and it’s helped me in more ways than not. My early 20’s were really hard for me and I’m not so sure I would’ve survived if it weren’t for the trust I had with my therapist. Therapy isn’t a joke and it’s not just for certain people in the world. I truly believe everyone would benefit from expressing their deepest fears, traumas, insecurities, and most importantly; who you actually want to be, rather than balancing between your old life and your new one. 

Anyone that knows me personally would probably say, “She’s a lot … kinda crazy … has a lot of boundaries … late everywhere 🥹 … stays up all night willingly because she wants to succeed that much … the kindest soul that is often misunderstood.” It’s been a challenge for me in this life trying to have boundaries and learn better behavior, while most people are stuck in who they always were and fail to realize the “accept me for me” aka the ‘tolerate all my bs because I’m not changing’ mindset is extremely toxic and unacceptable. 

The millenial generation has been forced to adapt and has seen a ton of change during our time on earth. The older generations from my perspective, struggle to view opinions outside of their own. Great relationships take time and require patience, as our thinking process has formed with what we have went through in life. How we have either adapted to failure, or allowed failure to consume us, has a lot to do with how we view ourselves and those around us. 

[continued in comments]
Stop placing yourself in the box they created to contain you.

The truth is, most of us want more out of life. Unfortunately, not many are prepared to fail a lot first. You’re not ready to be broke. You’re not ready to lose everyone. You’re not ready to have mental break down after mental break down, struggling to just survive. You’re not ready to meet pressure right in the face. 

Some of us choose to stay living in a nightmare because dealing with the turbulence is easier than change. The nightmare you choose to live in eventually becomes normal. Every time you open an app on your phone, it’s a constant reminder of your own wasted time. Instead of going after what you really want, you’re stuck watching those you look up to chase their goals day by day. 

A lot of us have dreams. Some have goals. Dreamers create an illusion of what can be. Those that have goals, practice having measurable data that is surrounded by time. Dreams to me is comparable to when I thought I could change someone just based off of my own influence. The potential was there, but it was never real. Goal oriented people are consistent and have the power to change their life. 

The first step in changing your life is believing you’re it first, before anyone else notices. You are talented. You are special. You are capable. The words we say become our life. Instead of watching other people be, “It,” why don’t you start practicing and believing… that you have what it takes to become IT?

Confidence vs. Arrogance 

What does that mean to you? Think about that for a moment. 

Confidence stems from knowing you are capable. Being able to differentiate your strengths and flaws. The ability to believe in yourself when no one else does. Doing what “can’t” or “shouldn’t” be done and accomplishing the ‘unheard’ of, creates confidence. The consistent actions repeated over and over, regardless of failure, is what allows one to know that the only real way to fail, is to stop. Confident people understand they have to face humiliation and accountability before seeing the W’s fall in line.

Arrogance is something you can just feel. Words don’t have to be said. Arrogant people are fake confident because their ego projects more than what they are aware/capable of. Arrogant people are “confident” about the unknown, where confident people are confident because they do. Arrogant people see themselves differently than everyone else. Arrogant people can’t be trusted. Facts are hard to prove when one chooses to live through projection of ego, than reality.

Now….. when you can combine confidence + ego because of the time, effort, and energy put in… now that’s successful. There is data to back up words and most importantly, actions. 

When you can learn to be confident, while being humiliated, while also failing, and maybe winning slightly… you’re on the right path 😉
